      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your description of an empty, hollow feeling instead of traditional grief is valid and speaks to a profound emotional numbness that often accompanies deep loss. When the mind collapses under the weight of unrequited sacrifice, it can feel easier to retreat into silence than to attempt healing. Please consider reaching out to a crisis line even if you don't feel like speaking; a professional counselor might simply listen without judgment to help you navigate this void safely. Your current desire to stop feeling is understandable, but prioritizing your safety and a small moment of rest is the only way forward at this time.",
