      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes absolute sense that you feel like quitting is the only way out when you have given everything only to face loss and now feel completely empty. It is incredibly heavy to ask yourself to be resilient when you are drowning, and the desire to stop existing feels like a logical conclusion to your pain. Please hear me clearly: while your feelings are understandable, the only exit that actually leads to relief is not closing your eyes forever, but finding a tiny, safe place to breathe so you can survive this unbearable night. You might be ready today, but you are not giving up on yourself permanently.",
